The course gives overview about main theories of society, explains the structure and functioning of society and culture, and discusses interrelations between individual, society and culture. In seminars the specific features of Estonian society and culture are thoroughly examined.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide overview about the main social processes and functioning of the society as in general, as well as in the context of Estonian society.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course, students: - know main concepts and theoretical approaches concerning culture and society: -	- understands the nature and structure of the society and its connections with the development of an individual and culture; - have overview about societal institutions and respective interrelations;  - are able to notice and understand specific features of Estonian society and to elate them with the historic, social, economic, political and cultural development; - have systematic overview about cultural developments in Estonia and can orientate in inner structure of Estonian cultural development.
